296
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:58,449
Sure you will,
just as soon as you learn how to read.

297
00:27:12,530 --> 00:27:14,259
Take off those shoes.

298
00:27:16,334 --> 00:27:18,928
My legs are not good enough for them?

299
00:27:19,304 --> 00:27:21,932
They're not good enough for your legs.

300
00:28:01,079 --> 00:28:04,310
Sorry what I called you.
I didn't mean what I said.

301
00:28:04,716 --> 00:28:06,274
I didn't either.

302
00:28:07,318 --> 00:28:09,616
-You got a car?
-No.

303
00:28:10,889 --> 00:28:13,153
I do. It's in the parking lot.

304
00:28:13,692 --> 00:28:15,990
It's a '27 convertible.

305
00:28:16,895 --> 00:28:20,991
The stuffing, it's a little bit
out of the upholstery, but it runs.

306
00:28:24,269 --> 00:28:25,827
I'm off at 11:00.

307
00:28:31,509 --> 00:28:33,067
Camilla Lombard?

308
00:28:42,887 --> 00:28:44,081
Arturo.

309
00:28:44,422 --> 00:28:47,186
-This is Sammy.
-Hi.

310
00:28:50,428 --> 00:28:51,952
Are you coming?

311
00:29:07,278 --> 00:29:08,870
Have a good night.

312
00:29:17,989 --> 00:29:19,718
Be right back.

313
00:29:53,458 --> 00:29:54,755
Who is he?

314
00:29:55,627 --> 00:29:58,926
Sammy? Just a friend.

315
00:29:59,564 --> 00:30:01,361
What kind of a friend?

316
00:30:03,268 --> 00:30:04,633
A good one.

317
00:30:05,804 --> 00:30:07,328
He got me my job.

318
00:30:09,107 --> 00:30:12,565
-They let the bartender hire you?
-Sammy's not just the bartender.

319
00:30:12,677 --> 00:30:15,578
Oh, yeah?
What else is he, a concert pianist?

320
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:19,675
Listen, Arturo,
you're not the only writer in town.

321
00:30:26,524 --> 00:30:29,357
-Sammy's a writer?
-You'd be surprised.

322
00:30:29,460 --> 00:30:32,122
I'd be surprised
if he could write his name.

323
00:30:32,230 --> 00:30:33,527
Do you like my car?

324
00:30:33,631 --> 00:30:36,031
How come it's registered to
Camilla Lombard? Your name's Lopez.

325
00:30:36,134 --> 00:30:37,726
-You married?
-No.

326
00:30:37,936 --> 00:30:40,427
-So what's the Lombard for?
-For fun.

327
00:30:40,572 --> 00:30:43,837
-Sometimes I use it professionally.
-As a waitress?

328
00:30:44,776 --> 00:30:46,403
Do you like your name?

329
00:30:46,511 --> 00:30:51,175
Don't you wish it was Johnson
or Williams or something?

330
00:30:51,883 --> 00:30:53,908
-No.
-Come on.

331
00:30:54,018 --> 00:30:56,782
Do you honestly like
being called Bandini?

332
00:30:57,655 --> 00:31:00,283
-I'm satisfied with my name.
-No, you're not.

333
00:31:00,391 --> 00:31:01,858
-I am.
-You're not.

334
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:02,984
-I am.
-You're not.

335
00:31:03,094 --> 00:31:04,721
-I am.
-You're not.

336
00:31:05,363 --> 00:31:08,355
What's Sammy's last name,
Johnson or Williams?

337
00:31:09,467 --> 00:31:10,627
White.

338
00:31:10,735 --> 00:31:13,795
Pretty much sums up your ambition
in life, doesn't it? To be Mrs. White?

339
00:31:13,905 --> 00:31:16,965
You can be a real son of a bitch,
you know that?

340
00:31:45,970 --> 00:31:47,938
-Are you still cold?
-No.

341
00:31:48,673 --> 00:31:50,641
The cliffs keep you warm.

342
00:31:52,277 --> 00:31:55,542
They're like a blanket
when you're underneath them.

343
00:31:59,417 --> 00:32:01,282
Why do you get so mean?

344
00:32:02,020 --> 00:32:03,851
Why do you get so mean?

345
00:32:14,632 --> 00:32:16,361
Can't we be friends?

346
00:32:22,307 --> 00:32:24,400
Friends like you and Sammy?

347
00:32:34,018 --> 00:32:35,610
Look at the fog.

348
00:32:40,458 --> 00:32:43,325
An army of ghosts crawling
on their bellies.

349
00:32:44,862 --> 00:32:46,921
What are you talking about?

350
00:32:47,365 --> 00:32:50,857
The fog bank.
It creeps in and hugs the water.

351
00:32:54,472 --> 00:32:58,033
-You didn't answer my question.
-I know what a fog bank is.

352
00:32:58,142 --> 00:32:59,507
And what about you and Sammy?

353
00:32:59,610 --> 00:33:02,204
Who are you interested in,
me or Sammy?

354
00:33:02,947 --> 00:33:06,144
Come on, why don't you teach me
how to ride a wave?

355
00:33:06,384 --> 00:33:08,477
Out there, in all this fog?

356
00:33:08,886 --> 00:33:10,353
Yeah, why not?

357
00:33:11,789 --> 00:33:13,313
Are you afraid?

358
00:33:14,726 --> 00:33:16,193
Of course not.

359
00:33:23,534 --> 00:33:25,502
What are you waiting for?

360
00:33:25,770 --> 00:33:29,035
Come in! Come here!

361
00:33:38,716 --> 00:33:40,946
Come here! Come on!

362
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:42,884
Get in here!

363
00:33:49,761 --> 00:33:51,456
What are you hiding?

364
00:33:52,497 --> 00:33:55,864
You got a pretty one.
Pink as a baby's bottom.

365
00:33:56,067 --> 00:33:58,126
Relax. Let's have some fun.

366
00:34:03,307 --> 00:34:07,573
-You're not gonna ride a wave tonight.
-Sure I will. You show me how.

367
00:34:07,678 --> 00:34:08,770
I'm from Colorado.

368
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:10,609
You mean you don't know
how to ride a wave?

369
00:34:10,715 --> 00:34:13,980
Listen. My technique might be not good
for you to learn. It's unorthodox.

370
00:34:14,085 --> 00:34:16,178
That's okay. I'd like to learn from you.

371
00:34:16,287 --> 00:34:19,120
The first thing you gotta do is
get to where the waves are.

372
00:34:19,223 --> 00:34:21,350
Don't take any chances.
Just stay back, stay right there.

373
00:34:21,459 --> 00:34:23,120
I will, I promise.

374
00:34:29,233 --> 00:34:31,064
Just watch me...

375
00:34:48,219 --> 00:34:51,017
-Help!
-Camilla!

376
00:34:52,723 --> 00:34:54,088
Camilla?

377
00:34:54,692 --> 00:34:58,150
Camilla! Camilla!

378
00:35:00,598 --> 00:35:03,431
Oh, God. Camilla!

379
00:35:14,512 --> 00:35:15,706
Camilla!

380
00:35:17,849 --> 00:35:20,113
Where'd she go? Where'd she go?

381
00:35:21,018 --> 00:35:22,781
Camilla! Camilla!

382
00:35:31,529 --> 00:35:32,723
Camilla!

383
00:35:41,873 --> 00:35:43,932
Fooled you pretty good!

384
00:35:45,810 --> 00:35:48,278
It was as good as your heart attack.

385
00:35:49,780 --> 00:35:52,908
-Admit it.
-It was better.

386
00:35:53,651 --> 00:35:56,711
You can dish it out,
but you can't take it, huh?

387
00:36:03,461 --> 00:36:04,860
Cut it out!

388
00:36:06,497 --> 00:36:10,695
It was a joke, God damn it!
What are you trying to do, drown me?

389
00:36:18,809 --> 00:36:22,006
I'll never forgive you.
Not for my whole life.

390
00:36:22,113 --> 00:36:24,274
I thought your life was over.

391
00:36:24,782 --> 00:36:27,683
I thought I was gonna die
looking for you.

392
00:36:28,319 --> 00:36:30,787
That was my first time in the ocean.

393
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:42,832
What you gonna do now, walk home?

394
00:36:42,934 --> 00:36:46,062
It's 10 miles to downtown.
Where do you live?

395
00:36:46,304 --> 00:36:47,771
The Alta Loma.

396
00:36:57,014 --> 00:36:58,242
Bunker Hill.

397
00:36:58,349 --> 00:37:01,512
Old women and weak men.
Perfect place for you.

398
00:37:01,619 --> 00:37:05,248
Couldn't be better.
In my hotel they don't allow Mexicans.

399
00:37:20,004 --> 00:37:21,369
White dough.

400
00:37:22,573 --> 00:37:25,007
No wonder she laughed. Who wouldn't?

401
00:37:25,610 --> 00:37:29,376
Arturo Bandini, genius,
man of the world,

402
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:33,348
can't take a walk on the beach
without trying to hide his dick.

403
00:37:38,189 --> 00:37:42,626
<i>I never wanted to see you again.</i>
<i>You were so mean last night.</i>

404
00:37:43,027 --> 00:37:44,187
<i>Get in.</i>

405
00:37:45,730 --> 00:37:46,992
<i>What for?</i>

406
00:37:48,966 --> 00:37:50,126
<i>Get in.</i>

407
00:38:04,949 --> 00:38:07,179
<i>Arturo, don't stop.</i>

408
00:38:07,285 --> 00:38:10,448
<i>Please don't ever stop. Arturo...</i>

409
00:38:14,058 --> 00:38:16,026
Jesus Christ, Hellfrick!

410
00:38:17,328 --> 00:38:19,762
Have you ever heard of knocking
before you come into a room?

411
00:38:19,864 --> 00:38:23,459
Sorry, kid. Didn't mean to disturb you.

412
00:38:24,335 --> 00:38:26,064
Artist at work, huh?

413
00:38:26,804 --> 00:38:28,203
Listen, kid.

414
00:38:30,207 --> 00:38:31,606
How much dough you got?

415
00:38:31,709 --> 00:38:35,338
-Oh, for Christ's sake!
-No, no, no, it's not for booze.

416
00:38:35,780 --> 00:38:39,011
-Well, then what's it for?
-Meat.

417
00:38:39,850 --> 00:38:40,908
Meat?

418
00:38:41,285 --> 00:38:45,278
